input_samples.description:
12 " x 5 " plate

Magnesium-aluminum-manganese alloy (AM series) plates were super vacuum die cast (SVDC) by Ford Research and Innovation Center at MagTech Corporation. The plates were cast on a Prince 836 high-pressure die casting machine with a Binary IIM shot system and Prince Prolink/Profiler process control and monitoring software.  The alloy was melted and held in an electric resistance furnace using a stainless steel crucible fitted with a cover.  The target melt temperature was 675â„ƒ.  Sulfur hexafluoride was used as the cover gas to prevent oxidation.  Molten magnesium was transferred from the furnace to the shot sleeve using a Metamag auger-type pump.
